## Supporting Types



<h4 id="placementstrategy">Placement<wbr>Strategy</h4>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="tabular"><dt>Spread</dt>
    <dd>spread<p>A <code>spread</code> placement group places instances on distinct hardware.</p>
</dd><dt>Cluster</dt>
    <dd>cluster<p>A <code>cluster</code> placement group is a logical grouping of instances within a single
Availability Zone that benefit from low network latency, high network throughput.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="go">
<dl class="tabular"><dt>Placement<wbr>Strategy<wbr>Spread</dt>
    <dd>spread<p>A <code>spread</code> placement group places instances on distinct hardware.</p>
</dd><dt>Placement<wbr>Strategy<wbr>Cluster</dt>
    <dd>cluster<p>A <code>cluster</code> placement group is a logical grouping of instances within a single
Availability Zone that benefit from low network latency, high network throughput.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="java">
<dl class="tabular"><dt>Spread</dt>
    <dd>spread<p>A <code>spread</code> placement group places instances on distinct hardware.</p>
</dd><dt>Cluster</dt>
    <dd>cluster<p>A <code>cluster</code> placement group is a logical grouping of instances within a single
Availability Zone that benefit from low network latency, high network throughput.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

## Import



Placement groups can be imported using the `name`, e.g.,

```sh
 $ pulumi import aws:ec2/placementGroup:PlacementGroup prod_pg production-placement-group
```
